id=dresosmicrog
name=DresOS microG
version=v2.0.0
versionCode=20000
author=DresOperatingSystems
description=Systemless microG suite with bundled signature spoofing, prebaked Google debloat, security hardening, and per component bootloop protection. Bundles GmsCore 0.3.7.250932, Companion FakeStore, GsfProxy, DroidGuard Helper, Aurora Store, Aurora Services privileged extension. APKs and matching privapp permissions XML land in the same partition (product priv-app on API 28 plus, system priv-app on API 26 and 27), satisfying Android 11 plus same partition enforcement. Cert identity is verified post boot via cmd package dump reading the X.509 cert SHA 256 PMS itself computes. Debloat runs at runtime via pm disable user, persisted in package restrictions and reversible by uninstall. The bootloop sentinel uses per stage markers so a single failed component is disabled on third strike without taking the whole module offline. ROMs that already ship upstream signed microG are autodetected and only Aurora plus DroidGuard are staged. Works on Android 8 through 16, arm, arm64, x86, x86_64. Coexists with the DresOS AOSmium WebView module. dresoperatingsystems.github.io
support=https://github.com/DresOperatingSystems/DresOS-Magisk-Modules/issues
updateJson=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/DresOperatingSystems/DresOS-Magisk-Modules/main/microg/update.json
minMagisk=24000
